    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/843.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Livingston</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cape Haitien</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<hi rend="italic">received</hi>
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" type="received-date" when="1914-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1914</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; undated.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Just received cablegram from President of Haiti requesting protection of family
                    here of Minister of Interior Charles Zamor. Have conferred with Commanders of
                        <hi rend="italic">San Francisco</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Wheeling</hi> and
                    we advise acceptance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Livingston</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
